properties.areaDesc: Chesapeake Bay north of Pooles Island MD; Tidal Potomac from Key Bridge to Indian Head MD; Patapsco River including Baltimore Harbor; Chesapeake Bay from Pooles Island to Sandy Point MD
properties.headline: Marine Weather Statement issued January 20 at 10:38AM EST by NWS Baltimore MD/Washington DC
properties.description:
Strong northwest winds will cause water levels to run one to two
feet below mean lower low water along the western shore of the
Chesapeake Bay from Pooles Island to Sandy Point, as well as
locations along the upper tidal Potomac around the time of low
tide this morning and early afternoon. Low tide at Fort McHenry
was at 8:36 AM, 10:34 AM at Alexandria, and 11:58 AM at Havre de
Grace.

Mariners should check navigation charts to avoid grounding their
vessel, particularly when boating away from the main channel..

NWSheadline: BLOWOUT TIDES THIS MORNING AND EARLY AFTERNOON
